Brussels Sprout Salad
--Cook's Country

3	tbsp lemon juice
2	tbsp dijon mustard
1	small shallot, minced
1	garlic clove, minced
salt and pepper
6	tbsp evoo
2	lbs Brussels sprouts, trimmed, halved, and sliced very thin
3	oz Pecorino Romano cheese, shredded (1 c)
½	c pine nuts, toasted

Whisk lemon juice, mustard, shallot, garlic, and ½ tsp salt together in large bowl. Slowly whisk in oil until incorporated. Toss Brussels sprouts with vinaigrette and let sit for at least 30 min or up to 2 hr. Fold in Pecorino and pine nuts. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Serve.

Notes: can try roasted hazelnuts instead of pine nuts, even add diced apple
